Contract milestones:
The specific Grinding Services to be provided are as follows:
- Main line grinding Services for all regions listed below
- Turnout grinding Services for all regions listed below
The following regions for rail grinding to be conducted is as follows
- South East Queensland (SEQ)
- North Coast Line NCL (North) - Cairns-Rockhampton
- North Coast Line NCL (Near North/South) - Parana - Tamaree
- GNR – Townsville to Mt Isa
- West Moreton System – Toowoomba to Columboola
The scope of services is to control the wheel rail interface so that rail grinding will:
- progressively establish rail profiles that optimise the wheel/rail interface condition to maximise the life of the rail and wheel asset,
- maintain rail profiles to optimise the rail/wheel interface to prevent the development of rail defects and
- remove or control existing rail surface defects and rail head metal flow.
The timeline to plan & deliver rail grinding Services shall be as outlined in the detailed Statement of Works. The stages of Services shall be planned in sufficient advance times to ensure that all of Queensland Rail’s possession planning, operational, freight business, environmental & safety requirements are timely met and also Queensland Rail’s resources are made available to support the rail grinding services delivered by the Contractor.
Contract performance management:
The performance is measured by the following KPIs:
Grind Quality Index (GQI) or similar
Performance/Efficient Delivery of Agreed Scope
Work Free of Lost Time Injuries (LTIs)
Work free of SPADs (Signal Passed At Danger)
Administration of the Agreement
